7 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
8 HOUSE AMENDMENT “ ” to COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “A” to S.P. 47, L.D.
9 30, “Resolve, Directing the Department of Transportation to Implement the
10 Recommendations of the Portland to Auburn Rail Use Advisory Council Regarding the
11 Rail Line from Portland to Yarmouth ”
12 Amend the amendment by inserting after section 1 the following:
13 'Sec. 2. Limitation on removal of track. Resolved: That the Department of
14 Transportation may not remove any portion of the railroad track described in section 1 for
15 which there is a pending request for proposals application from a train company or any
16 other commercial enterprise proposing to use that portion of the railroad track.
17 Sec. 3. Use of state funding or state bonds prohibited. Resolved: That the
18 Department of Transportation may not use funding provided by the State or funding
19 obtained through the sale of bonds issued by the State for the purposes of removing railroad
20 track pursuant to section 1.'
21 Amend the amendment by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or
22 section number to read consecutively.
23 SUMMARY
2244 This amendment amends Committee Amendment "A." The amendment prohibits the
2255 Department of Transportation from removing any portion of the railroad track for which
2266 there is a pending request for proposals application from a train company or any other
2277 commercial enterprise proposing to use that portion of the railroad track. The amendment
2288 also prohibits the department from using any funding provided by the State or funding
2299 obtained through the sale of bonds issued by the State for the purposes of removing the
3300 railroad track that the department is directed to remove under the committee amendment.
